title: College cross country: Macaulay named Region 3 athlete of the week
text:
A A 
Jefferson Community College womenâ€™s cross country runner Kurstyn Macaulay was named the Region 3 Athlete of the Week on Wednesday. 
Macaulay, a sophomore from Alexandria Bay, won the Mid-State Athletic Conference championship race last Saturday, completing the 5K course at Finger Lakes Community College in 21 minutes and 48.1 seconds. 
Macaulay, who beat the second-place finisher by more than a minute, also led the Cannoneers to the team title and was named the MSAC Runner of the Year on Monday.
